
[1]stubbornness

   STUBBORNNESS, n.

   1. Perverse and unreasonable obstinacy; inflexibility; contumacy.

   Stubbornness and obstinate disobedience must be mastered with blows.

   2. Stiffness; want of pliancy.

   3. Refractoriness, as of ores.
